During warming over the weekend the snowpack has been affected across the country, initially making it unstable, but stabilizing when it freezes. Weak layers have been observed in the Eastfjords, Westfjords, and North Iceland and these weaknesses may still be present, especially in the North where temperatures has been lower and less precipitation. A snowmobiler triggered an avalanche above F&aacute;skr&uacute;&eth;sfj&ouml;r&eth;ur on Wednesday. Snowmobilers traveling through Flateyjarskagi en route to Keflav&iacute;k encountered four very wide avalanches that fell on February 16th on north- and west-facing slopes. Widespread weakness is still found in North Iceland at the interfaces of ice layers and new wind slabs, especially on north- and south-facing slopes where snow has drifted in recent days.





